{"tid":35676,"cid":5,"subCid":0,"title":"牛津籲學生棄用she、he　以「ze」稱呼跨性別同學","createTime":"2016-12-12T08:41:14.000Z","updateTime":"2016-12-12T14:00:25.000Z","uid":51546,"like":2,"dislike":2,"uniUserReply":0,"replies":[{"pid":"0f33fd10e4e940adf4ed5b720cc082900f0c9450","tid":35676,"uid":51546,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2016-12-12T08:41:14.000Z","msg":"即時新聞國際<br />\n<br />\n選擇分類&nbsp;<br />\n<br />\n牛津籲學生棄用she、he　以「ze」稱呼跨性別同學<br />\n<br />\n2016-12-12 10:31&nbsp;文字大小<br />\n<br />\n￼<br />\n<br />\n1/1轉自英國每日郵報<br />\n<br />\n英國牛津大學歷史最悠久之一的學生組織辯論學會（Oxford Union），呼籲學生在稱呼跨性別同學時，使用代名詞「ze」，代替she和he。<br />\n<br />\n牛津大學一向鼓勵性別多元，辯論學會在宣傳單張上呼籲學生用「ze」稱呼跨性別同學，減少跨性別人士遭歧視的機會。學會又稱，希望「ze」可以應用於課堂上。根據大學的行為守則，使用錯誤的代名詞稱呼跨性別人士屬於歧視。<br />\n<br />\n爭取LGBT（同性戀、雙性戀及跨性別）權益人士塔切爾（Peter Tatchell）表示，淡化性別差異和障礙是一件好事，部分人亦渴望用中性代名詞被稱呼，不過措施毋須強制執行。"},{"pid":"b307b96caf1c3f069bae6557b3eb3d88e8bcdae3","tid":35676,"uid":90,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2016-12-12T08:41:49.000Z","msg":"左膠<img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/dead.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" />"},{"pid":"b545115ffc38d877468fbfc9f9ad699442592e56","tid":35676,"uid":20943,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2016-12-12T08:42:09.000Z","msg":"<img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/dead.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /> 多鳩餘"},{"pid":"67d3ffbe985ad56976bcbe73493e983d00037471","tid":35676,"uid":235,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2016-12-12T08:44:26.000Z","msg":"此回覆已被刪除"},{"pid":"7ec68f4654165dd93fb22ef633a0c3ec48c56a4b","tid":35676,"uid":28068,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2016-12-12T08:45:07.000Z","msg":"我淨係想知點讀<img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/wonder.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" />"},{"pid":"9e122ba789c01f80aca9ddac0a641403ce91fc93","tid":35676,"uid":2259,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2016-12-12T08:45:08.000Z","msg":"好似支那拼音咁<img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/dead.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" />"},{"pid":"ef0a0f937b80a41585095f2d47131685ae688cc6",